                            <comment id="15052567" author="anoop.hbase" created="Fri, 11 Dec 2015 10:08:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That will be bad that depending on Quota is enabled or not, we have diff ACL permission need for creating a table. We should support old permission way for creation of table (if Quota is there or not)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15062020" author="ashish singhi" created="Thu, 17 Dec 2015 13:14:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=anoop.hbase&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;anoop.hbase&quot;&gt;Anoop Sam John&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mbertozzi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mbertozzi&quot;&gt;Matteo Bertozzi&lt;/a&gt;, any suggestion how to handle this if not document update ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15062053" author="anoop.hbase" created="Thu, 17 Dec 2015 13:53:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The quota check should be done as a super user who will have all permission.  Already at some point, we do the create table flow with User.doAs() right? Need to see...  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15062054" author="anoop.hbase" created="Thu, 17 Dec 2015 13:53:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IMO we must fix this and not simple document update.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15062421" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Thu, 17 Dec 2015 17:49:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In the above example, step 3 used default namespace whereas step granted permission for namespace ns1. Please perform table creation in namespace ns1 and update the stack trace.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15074904" author="ashish singhi" created="Wed, 30 Dec 2015 10:17:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With procedure v2 I am not getting this issue. So this affects only 1.1.x when procedure v2 is disabled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
